This series is somewhat unique for Stratechery in that my interview subject=
s are generally not investors; this series, though, started in October 2022=
, when Friedman and Gross were launching a grant program, precisely because=
 we shared a sense that there wasn't nearly enough activity or discussion a=
round AI; one month later ChatGPT came out and the world has changed dramat=
ically, including for Friedman and Gross, who are two of the leading invest=
ors in the space. Gross is also now the CEO of Safe Superintelligence Inc.,=
 which we do not discuss in this interview. To that end, I think it has bee=
n very valuable =E2=80=94 and popular =E2=80=94=C2=A0to continue this serie=
s, but do keep in mind that Friedman and Gross may be invested in some of t=
he companies we discuss.

The amount of AI news since the last interview in this series has been subs=
tantial, and we get to as much of it as we can, including discussing the ra=
te of AI diffusion and potential bubble dynamics, Stargate and DeepSeek, Ro=
botics, and where Big Tech stands currently. We also, as is our wont, get i=
nto some more philosophical questions, including the implications of believ=
ing in AGI, the importance of personality, and the battle for the future of=
 language and culture inherent in these models.

As a reminder, all Stratechery content, including interviews, is available =
as a podcast; click the link at the top of this email to add Stratechery to=
 your podcast player.

